rComments: Great course with the exact amount of information. The teacher is open to answer any question and the exercices provides a great aproach to the theme. Exigent but fair in the exams

Well-intended professor, I guess but the saying is true: "Hell is paved with good intentions." Seems to never question himself, to think that it looks bad on a teacher to admit his mistakes. If you wanna pass his class, just keep in mind that his teachings are gospel-truth, be both a parrot and a sheep. Don't use your brain too much!

Summer course for International Commercial Transactions. Can't comment on much because I dropped the class after the first lecture because he was totally incomprehensible, boring and the work load was ridiculous. Others who remained told me I was lucky to have dropped the course.
